Process Engineer (1st, 2nd, 3rd Shift Positions)

soulbrain MI

- Northville, MI 48168

POSITION SUMMARY: Responsible for the on time manufacturing of customized, high quality, lithium ion electrolyte with zero safety incidents.
RESPONSIBILITIES AND DUTIES:
· Produces custom electrolyte formulations using varying methods based on customer requirements.
· Maintains physical inventory.
· Determines and maintains all levels of production supports supplies.
· Ensures process equipment is fully functional by performing routine maintenance.
· Assists in resolving all product-related quality issues.
· Performs all tasks according to standard operating procedures.
· Follows all company, industry standard and OSHA safety procedures, including equipment safety and personal protective equipment (PPE).
· Supports other departments, as needed.
EDUCATION AND WORK EXPERIENCE:
· Bachelor’s degree in chemical engineering or related field.
· 1-3 years experience working in a manufacturing setting preferred.
SKILLS:
· Knowledge of safe hazardous material handling policies and procedures.
· Ability to operate material handling equipment and lift or move 50+ lbs.
· Ability to make presentations to small and large groups.
· Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Office.
